been with the Camden P.D.

29:58.500 --> 30:03.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He ordered his officers to leave
their cars, patrol neighborhoods
on foot, knock on doors,

30:05.466 --> 30:09.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
look in on shopkeepers, get
to know and become known
to the people they served.

30:12.300 --> 30:17.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SCOTT THOMSON, Camden, New
Jersey, Police Chief: We saw,
almost instantaneously, a change

30:18.866 --> 30:22.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in the atmosphere
within neighborhoods.

30:22.566 --> 30:27.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's what people wanted
from us, and it has helped us
significantly, and for us to

30:29.000 --> 30:31.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
provide better policing
services to them as well.

30:31.766 --> 30:36.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One, we have greater lines of
communication now, which has
given us a tremendous ability

30:38.633 --> 30:41.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to not only solve crime,
but prevent crime from
occurring in the first place.

30:41.833 --> 30:45.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The
statistics back that up.

30:45.866 --> 30:50.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Since transitioning from the
old force to the new in 2014,
the number of murders dropped

30:50.366 --> 30:55.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by almost 70 percent,
burglaries by 27 percent,
robberies 33 percent,
and even an eye-catching

30:57.533 --> 31:02.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
143 percent spike in rapes that
the department attributes to
increased reporting, as well

31:04.066 --> 31:06.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
as new broader federal
guidelines on what
constitutes rape.

31:06.866 --> 31:11.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Overall, the city's
crime numbers are the
lowest in decades.

31:11.166 --> 31:15.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Those are impressive statistics
for any police department, and
residents don't dispute them.

31:15.800 --> 31:20.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But some say seeing them
in a report vs. feeling
the difference every
day are two different

31:20.533 --> 31:21.666 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
things.

31:21.666 --> 31:24.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: I see prostitutes
on my street.

31:24.066 --> 31:28.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I see drug transactions
on my street, in broad
daylight, every day.

31:28.800 --> 31:32.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: This local
business owner was one of
several people who asked not to

31:32.433 --> 31:37.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be identified, citing
concerns that his remarks
could complicate relations
with local police

31:38.166 --> 31:39.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
officers he knows.

31:39.666 --> 31:43.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The crimes, he suspects, are
visible to police as well.

31:43.333 --> 31:48.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: Those must be caught on
camera, but I can't tell that
it makes a lot of difference

31:51.000 --> 31:54.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in how much of it or
little of it is happening.

31:54.400 --> 31:58.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Surveillance
cameras are a major piece
of Chief Thomson's formula.

31:58.733 --> 32:02.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Some 200 of them are
deployed throughout the city.

32:02.366 --> 32:05.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The chief showed us the
Central command Center.

32:05.700 --> 32:10.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On these screens are the
real-time video feeds
from every camera, the
location of every officer

32:11.600 --> 32:13.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on patrol.

32:13.600 --> 32:17.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are also gunshot-detecting
microphones placed at certain
locations, meaning police

32:20.133 --> 32:25.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
know the location of the shots
to within a few meters seconds
after it happens, and can

32:26.300 --> 32:29.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
begin responding before
anyone even calls 911.

32:29.300 --> 32:32.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Still, not everyone is won over.

32:32.033 --> 32:36.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A Camden resident sees both
the opportunities and costs
of increased surveillance.

32:36.533 --> 32:41.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: I feel it's a violation
of civil rights, on some level,
with the cameras, because now

32:43.566 --> 32:47.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you're unknowingly filming
people who didn't give you
permission to film them.

32:49.233 --> 32:53.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I have also been on the side
where family members has lost
other family members to violence

32:56.133 --> 33:01.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the cameras had assisted
in the apprehension of the
person who committed the crime.

33:03.133 --> 33:06.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: If the police department
came to me and said, you're
going to have to give up all

33:08.566 --> 33:12.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
your privacy, but we're going
to reduce crime, then make you
a little bit safer, I would

33:12.633 --> 33:13.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
probably say no.

33:13.900 --> 33:16.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Nobody came to me
and asked me that.

33:16.000 --> 33:19.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Is there
a concern that people could
feel like their civil rights

33:19.200 --> 33:20.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
are being violated?

33:20.700 --> 33:24.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: We don't have any secret
cameras stored away in the city.

33:24.500 --> 33:25.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Everything is overt.

33:25.500 --> 33:27.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're up there on a pole.

33:27.033 --> 33:29.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They're not hidden.

33:29.100 --> 33:32.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we're sensitive to the fact
that there's people that may
not necessarily want the camera

33:32.433 --> 33:33.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
there.

33:33.933 --> 33:36.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But what we have found is the
majority of people do want them.

33:36.000 --> 33:40.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN:
Another major focus of
reform is de-escalation,
training officers to use

33:42.833 --> 33:47.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
force only as a last resort,
a tactic that played out
dramatically in this video shot

33:47.933 --> 33:49.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
two years ago.

33:49.966 --> 33:54.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A man was wielding a knife at a
restaurant, then began walking
down the street brandishing

33:54.633 --> 33:56.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the weapon.

33:56.666 --> 33:59.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Rather than taking him down,
police formed a containment
bubble around him, then followed

33:59.366 --> 34:02.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
him for blocks until
he could be disarmed.

34:02.200 --> 34:06.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That restraint and patience
earned praise from the chief.

34:06.300 --> 34:09.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SCOTT THOMSON: We're
handling them exactly
the way that we want to.

34:09.333 --> 34:14.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And at the end of the day,
you know, what's happening is,
more people are being returned

34:14.000 --> 34:16.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to their family.

34:16.000 --> 34:20.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And every time that an
officer pulls the trigger,
it's life-altering for them.

34:22.633 --> 34:25.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: His
department's records show
that, since 2014, the
frequency of officers

34:25.566 --> 34:28.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
using force has
dropped by 24 percent.

34:28.766 --> 34:33.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And citizen complaints
of police using excessive
force are down 49 percent.

34:33.400 --> 34:36.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But do these methods put an
officer's own life at risk?

34:36.633 --> 34:39.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: Sir, drop the knife,
or I will Tase you.

34:39.866 --> 34:44.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SCOTT THOMSON: What we're
telling officers to do is slow
it down, is -- that which we're

34:46.766 --> 34:50.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
training officers to do is
actually safer for the officers,
when, historically, officers

34:52.533 --> 34:56.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
have been rushing into
situations because
that's the training we
provide, and it's been

34:56.233 --> 35:01.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
dangerous for them, and often
leaving them with the only
option that's left is deadly

35:02.566 --> 35:04.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
force.

35:04.633 --> 35:07.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: That's
counter to the more
militarized approaches
taken by other cities.

35:07.866 --> 35:09.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What's the hardest part
about changing culture?

35:09.933 --> 35:14.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SCOTT THOMSON: So, for
us, it was that transition
from warrior to guardian.

35:14.000 --> 35:19.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You still have to have
the warrior mentality and
the ability to trigger
that warrior element

35:20.800 --> 35:22.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
when the time calls for it.

35:22.500 --> 35:26.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
However, that shouldn't
be your operating premise.

35:26.366 --> 35:28.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That should be the anomaly.

35:28.033 --> 35:29.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right?

35:29.200 --> 35:30.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That should be the
exception, not the rule.

35:30.800 --> 35:34.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The rule should be,
you're a guardian.

35:34.233 --> 35:36.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You're in this neighborhood.

35:36.200 --> 35:38.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Throughout
this story, I spoke to a number
of people sitting on their

35:38.633 --> 35:43.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
stoops and sitting on their
porches, but none of them
wanted to talk to me on camera.

35:45.600 --> 35:48.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It wasn't because they felt
that the new police practices
were helping their neighborhood

35:48.000 --> 35:49.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
or hurting.

35:49.000 --> 35:51.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It was a mixed bag.

35:51.066 --> 35:55.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was because they felt
that talking to me would
invite unwanted attention.

35:55.133 --> 35:57.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Some feared a police they
still didn't fully trust.

35:57.566 --> 36:02.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And others feared drug
dealers, who may have
left street corners, but
are now behind closed

36:03.033 --> 36:05.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
doors.

36:05.133 --> 36:07.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIM GALLAGHER, Social Worker:
There were just dime bags and
needles all over the place.

36:07.100 --> 36:09.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Tim
Gallagher is a social worker
at Guadalupe Family Services.

36:09.366 --> 36:13.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He works on a block that's
seen tremendous improvement,
but he is still cautious.

36:13.900 --> 36:18.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TIM GALLAGHER: I think
their Manning concerns
are that it could happen
again, that the good

36:20.833 --> 36:22.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
cops who are here will leave,
and that other cops will replace
them who won't really know

36:22.966 --> 36:25.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the neighborhood.

36:25.033 --> 36:28.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Good cops
like Vidal Rivera, who is 6-0 in
the ring, undefeated, but knows

36:30.833 --> 36:33.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the fight for the streets
of his hometown is
just getting started.

36:33.733 --> 36:38.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm Hari Sreenivasan
in Camden, New Jersey.

36:44.166 --> 36:49.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And to the
analysis of Shields and Brooks.

36:51.700 --> 36:56.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's syndicated columnist
Mark Shields and New York
Times columnist David Brooks.

36:56.466 --> 36:58.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Welcome, gentlemen.

36:58.000 --> 37:00.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
David is joining us from
the Rocky Mountains,
Aspen, Colorado.

37:00.433 --> 37:04.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, let's start, both of you,
by talking about health care.

37:04.166 --> 37:08.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mark, we just heard a little
while ago on the program
Senator Roy Blunt of Missouri

37:08.166 --> 37:12.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
saying it's going to be hard,
he said, to get to 50 votes.

37:12.300 --> 37:14.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What are you hearing?

37:14.266 --> 37:18.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: It's an
understatement by Senator Blunt,
a masterpiece of understatement.

37:19.633 --> 37:22.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Judy, never say never.

37:22.766 --> 37:25.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I think it's about
time to say never.

37:25.233 --> 37:28.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I mean, this is not
being put together.

37:28.466 --> 37:33.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Quite frankly, the motion to
proceed, not to get inside
baseball, but that's when the

37:33.100 --> 37:36.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
majority leader -- means
bringing up a bill.

37:36.233 --> 37:41.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I have never seen a motion
to proceed, which is just
asking that the bill be brought

37:41.966 --> 37:44.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
up for debate, fail.

37:44.066 --> 37:48.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Mitch McConnell's
reputation as an inside
player has taken a big hit.

37:48.666 --> 37:52.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But there is not -- there is
not majority on what to do.

37:52.766 --> 37:55.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And it's not there.

37:55.433 --> 38:00.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I will just back to
one Republican has spoken
the absolute abject
truth on this subject.

38:02.500 --> 38:05.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he said, "In the 25 years
I have served in the Congress,
Republicans have never, not

38:05.500 --> 38:08.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
one time ever agreed
on a health care plan."

38:08.833 --> 38:11.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That was Speaker John
Boehner this year.

38:11.833 --> 38:13.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I think it remains true.

38:13.233 --> 38:15.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: David,
what are you picking up?

38:15.600 --> 38:20.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes, I'm hearing
negative vibes, but not
quite as negative as Mark.

38:20.466 --> 38:22.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I still think there's a chance.

38:22.833 --> 38:26.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What you hear is frustration
over, one, it's hard
to take away a benefit
people have already

38:26.933 --> 38:28.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
been given by law.

38:28.966 --> 38:32.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Two, the Republicans are
more ideologically divided
than they thought they were.

38:32.200 --> 38:35.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Three, it's very hard to pass
a bill without a White House.

38:35.733 --> 38:39.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the president basically
ineffective here, and the
vice president barely more so.

38:39.766 --> 38:41.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And so they're trying
to do it without him.

38:41.900 --> 38:45.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I think what they're
beginning to hear, as
the calls come in, is
that this is a proposal

38:45.733 --> 38:48.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that hits a lot of
Republicans really hard.

38:48.066 --> 38:52.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you're a 60-year-old white
male in Ohio, this can be
devastating to you, both in the

38:52.466 --> 38:57.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
coverage loss and in
the deductibles and the
out-of-pocket expenses,
so the calls are coming

38:57.400 --> 38:58.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
into the offices.

38:58.633 --> 39:00.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And that's making
people skittish.

39:00.633 --> 39:02.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I think it's an uphill fight.

39:02.066 --> 39:04.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I don't think it's quite
as impossible maybe.

39:04.566 --> 39:07.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I was
struck, Mark, that Senator
Blunt was saying the
more the senators learn

39:07.800 --> 39:09.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
about what's in here,
the harder it gets.

39:09.733 --> 39:10.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: That's right.

39:10.733 --> 39:12.800 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

39:12.800 --> 39:15.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
No, that's absolutely -- and
I would just add to it, Judy,
there is no public argument,

39:15.266 --> 39:17.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a case to be made for this.

39:17.466 --> 39:22.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Senator Blunt answered
your specific questions
well, but there is no --
there is not a rallying

39:24.433 --> 39:28.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
cry for, whether it's
preexisting condition
or, you know, that
everybody's child can be

39:29.633 --> 39:32.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on until the age of 26.

39:32.133 --> 39:36.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Obamacare, the
Affordable Care Act, they
could make a public case
for it, that everybody

39:37.566 --> 39:39.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
is in, that rates
will not be higher.

39:39.933 --> 39:41.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There's none here.

39:41.766 --> 39:43.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I think that's
a real problem.

39:43.866 --> 39:47.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
David's point about there
is no political air cover
from the White House.

39:47.700 --> 39:48.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Quite the opposite.

39:48.933 --> 39:52.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I mean, the White House
has been a liability.

39:52.033 --> 39:57.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president has been
unhelpful, uninformed,
and this morning tweeting,
let's repeal, which,

40:01.733 --> 40:06.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CBO, the Congressional Budget
Office, has a score on, would
put 26 million people uninsured

40:11.433 --> 40:15.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
