42:05.733 --> 42:09.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he back -- he hollered
backed at the governor,
at which point the
president's own political

42:09.766 --> 42:14.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
action committee, staffed
by the president's own
political aides and
apparatchiks, organized

42:17.300 --> 42:22.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a $1 million, expressed attack
ad series on him, Heller,
which Senator Thune objected

42:24.833 --> 42:27.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to, that Senator
McConnell opposed.

42:27.233 --> 42:31.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is the political equivalent
of coming down from the hills
and shooting the wounded.

42:31.633 --> 42:34.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And so they had to back off.

42:34.500 --> 42:38.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so you talk about White
House-congressional relations.

42:38.166 --> 42:41.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I mean, this is just -- it's
more than counterproductive.

42:41.833 --> 42:42.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's stupid.

42:42.833 --> 42:45.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You're right.

42:45.033 --> 42:47.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Senator Thune -- David,
Senator Thune's comment,
that wouldn't be a good
time to go after members

42:47.666 --> 42:48.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of your own party.

42:48.833 --> 42:50.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes.

42:50.300 --> 42:52.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

42:52.366 --> 42:56.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
No, it's -- the relations are
-- it's interesting to watch
even the reactions to the tweets

42:57.066 --> 42:58.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and everything else.

42:58.266 --> 43:00.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They can't get
away from this guy.

43:00.333 --> 43:02.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And what's been interesting,
talking to members of Congress,
is, it would be one thing if

43:02.366 --> 43:07.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he would just sort of disappear,
but they have to spend so much
of their time just reacting.

43:09.266 --> 43:11.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's just very hard to make
policy, aside from the problem
of just making policy from

43:11.800 --> 43:13.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Capitol Hill, which is
difficult to start with.

43:13.866 --> 43:18.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, speaking
of the tweets, David, we have
seen some eyebrow-raisers.

43:19.566 --> 43:21.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have heard some gasps.

43:21.666 --> 43:25.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I guess the president's
tweet yesterday morning about
the "Morning Joe" MSNBC cable

43:26.933 --> 43:31.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hosts, Joe Scarborough and
Mika Brzezinski, where the
president tweeted very personal

43:31.200 --> 43:36.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
insults, low I.Q.,
face-lift, and so forth, it
seemed to reach a new low.

43:38.733 --> 43:42.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Do we learn anything new about
this president at this point?

43:42.133 --> 43:46.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Well, one of the
nice things, if we can find a
silver lining here, is, it's

43:46.766 --> 43:51.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
possible for everybody
to be freshly appalled,
that we are not inured
to savage, misogynistic

43:53.900 --> 43:55.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
behavior of this sort.

43:55.366 --> 43:57.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I saw a lot
of people around.

43:57.433 --> 44:01.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And I certainly felt in
myself a freshness, a
freshness of outrage.

44:01.600 --> 44:06.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I must say, when I hear
Roy Blunt say it's unhelpful
to himself, well, that's true,

44:06.100 --> 44:09.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but it's more than
unhelpful to Donald Trump
to tweet in this way.

44:09.033 --> 44:10.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's morally objectionable.

44:10.300 --> 44:12.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I do wish more
senators would say that.

44:12.833 --> 44:16.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Lindsey Graham and Ben
Sasse have said it, but
a lot of others, oh,
it's just not helpful.

44:16.566 --> 44:18.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's more than that.

44:18.000 --> 44:20.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And the issue here is the
corruption of our public sphere.

44:20.800 --> 44:23.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's what Donald Trump
does with these things.

44:23.100 --> 44:26.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it makes it harder for us,
our country, to ever get back
to normal, when these things

44:26.433 --> 44:28.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are corrosive to just the way
people talk to each other.

44:28.900 --> 44:31.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Corruption
of the public sphere, Mark.

44:31.100 --> 44:34.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: I think David
is guilty of understatement.

44:34.266 --> 44:38.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
No, I think he put it very well.

44:38.066 --> 44:40.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This is hateful
and it's hurtful.

44:40.766 --> 44:45.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Judy, I don't know what
a parent or a grandparent
is supposed to say to a
10-year-old or a 12-year-old

44:47.700 --> 44:51.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
