this and was sent -- banished
to their room or whatever

44:53.800 --> 44:57.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
else for it, I mean, that the
president of the United States
can talk this way, and there

44:58.333 --> 45:00.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
are no consequences.

45:00.833 --> 45:05.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The irony is that he's more
engaged on the back-and-forth
with Joe Scarborough and Mika

45:07.933 --> 45:12.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Brzezinski on this than
he has been on health
care or any other issue.

45:14.066 --> 45:16.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He obviously -- this
is what matters to him.

45:16.733 --> 45:21.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's just that classic
-- not to be sectionally
biased, but it's sort
of a New York bully

45:24.833 --> 45:29.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
approach to life, I mean,
that you say anything,
you do anything, because
the important thing

45:30.433 --> 45:32.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is winning.

45:32.466 --> 45:36.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I just -- you know, I
don't know what else there is
to say, other than you want

45:38.900 --> 45:41.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to put yourself through a
car wash after you listen to
the president talk this way.

45:41.600 --> 45:43.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Are there
consequences, David?

45:43.733 --> 45:47.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I mean, I heard what you
said about some senators
are just saying, well,
it's not helpful, but

45:47.800 --> 45:52.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
other senators are going
further and saying,
this is really wrong.

45:53.666 --> 45:56.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But are there ever consequences?

45:56.366 --> 45:57.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Do we just go on like this?

45:57.733 --> 45:59.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes.

45:59.633 --> 46:02.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, we will see if
people eventually get
disappointed and get tired.

46:02.433 --> 46:06.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I do think if it -- one of the
things that may begin to offend
people is potential mafioso

46:06.933 --> 46:08.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
behavior.

46:08.866 --> 46:11.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One of the things we heard
this morning in the op-ed
piece in The Washington Post by

46:11.033 --> 46:16.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the two hosts was that the
White House sort of threatened
sort of extortion, that, if

46:18.000 --> 46:21.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
